<%# Phase 7.5 §11b — channel show page revamp.
    Three pane rows stacked vertically (detail → analytics → videos),
    replacing the prior two-pane URL+videos placeholder. Every
    nullable column has a muted empty-state per the locked matrix;
    the page never 500s on a bare-bones pre-sync channel.

    Unit A0 — channel is a read-only mirror (YouTube → pito). There is
    no edit affordance and no diff-reconciliation banner; the only
    mutable channel attribute is `star` (toggled from the pane view).
%>
<% display_title = channel_display_title(@channel) %>
<%# 2026-05-11 — drop the redundant "channel " prefix from the page title
    and breadcrumb. The `[channels]` breadcrumb segment already communicates
    the section; doubling "channel" in the leaf label is noise. %>
<% content_for(:title, display_title) %>
<% breadcrumb(["channels", channels_path], display_title) %>
<% content_for(:breadcrumb_actions) do %>
  <div class="dot-list">
    <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "changes", href: channel_change_logs_path(@channel))) %>
    <%# Unit A0 — channel is a read-only mirror; `[sync]` runs the
        one-way `ChannelSync` cache pull (the overwrite intent). There
        is no diff-check intent for channels anymore. %>
    <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "sync", href: "/syncs/channel/#{@channel.id}", data: { keyboard_page_action: "sync" })) %>
    <%# Phase 24 — per-channel `[revoke]` cascade. Inline with the rest
        of the heading-actions row. Destructive (red) — opens the
        wide-modal confirmation page. NO keyboard shortcut by design
        (locked decision #6, matches absence of shortcut for `[-]`). %>
    <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "revoke", href: revoke_channel_path(@channel), destructive: true)) %>
    <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "-", href: "/deletions/channel/#{@channel.id}", destructive: true, data: { keyboard_page_action: "delete" })) %>
  </div>
<% end %>

<%# `data-keyboard-external-url` keeps the `v` shortcut wired to the
    underlying YouTube URL (mirrors the CLI binding). The
    `data-keyboard-detail-prev-url` / `data-keyboard-detail-next-url`
    pair (when present) carries the `h` / `l` sibling navigation URLs
    for the global keyboard controller. %>
<div data-controller="add-pane" data-keyboard-external-url="<%= @channel.channel_url %>" <%= keyboard_detail_nav_data_attributes(@channel, scope: Channel, path_helper: method(:channel_path)) %>>
  <%# 2026-05-11 — title row is `<display_title> [+] · [YouTube]
      [Studio]`. The "channel" prefix was dropped from the H1
      (the [channels] breadcrumb segment already names the section).
      The outbound YouTube links moved up from the detail pane into
      the H1 row so the high-value navigation sits at the top edge of
      the page. A `nav-sep` middle-dot separates the in-app `[+]`
      action from the outbound `[YouTube][Studio]` cluster — same
      separator pattern used in the top navbar. Labels are the bare
      proper-noun brand + product name (no redundant "youtube"
      prefix on `[Studio]`, no redundant "channel" suffix on
      `[YouTube]`). %>
  <div class="dot-list" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
    <h1 style="display: inline;"><%= display_title %></h1>
    <% if @available_channels.any? %>
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "+", href: "#", data: { action: "click->add-pane#open" })) %>
    <% end %>
    <% yt_channel = youtube_channel_url(@channel) %>
    <% yt_studio = youtube_studio_url(@channel) %>
    <% if yt_channel || yt_studio %>
      <span class="nav-sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
      <%# 2026-05-16 polish — component auto-detects external hrefs;
          callers drop the explicit target/rel pair. %>
      <% if yt_channel %>
        <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "YouTube", href: yt_channel)) %>
      <% end %>
      <% if yt_studio %>
        <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(label: "Studio", href: yt_studio)) %>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <%# Phase 22 — in-flight import badge. Visible whenever an ImportJob
      for this channel is `queued` or `running`. Links to the modal's
      show view so the user can resume the keep/reject flow without
      reopening from `/videos`. %>
  <% if (in_flight_job = @channel.in_flight_import_job) %>
    <div class="pane pane--standalone" style="margin-bottom: 8px; padding: 6px 10px;">
      <%= render(Imports::ProgressIndicatorComponent.new(import_job: in_flight_job)) %>
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(
        label: "view progress",
        href: imports_channel_path(in_flight_job)
      )) %>
    </div>
  <% end %>

  <%# Row 1 — detail pane. Banner → avatar + headline (title, meta line,
      description) → links cluster. Banner row is hidden when
      `banner_url` is nil (locked decision: no colored placeholder).

      2026-05-11 (later) — the detail pane was retuned to match
      YouTube's channel-header geometry on desktop: a wide
      `aspect-ratio: 6.2 / 1` banner up top, then a flex row with a
      160px circular avatar on the LEFT and the headline stack on
      the RIGHT (large title, muted `@handle · N subscribers · M
      videos` meta line, description). The pito monospace + light
      theme + bracketed-link conventions stay; only sizing and
      positioning mirror YouTube.

      2026-05-11 (width fix) — switched from `pane--standalone` (auto
      width that stretches to its container) to `pane--wide` (the
      established 904px double-width modifier). 904px = 2 × 452px,
      so this row's single pane matches the total width of row 2's
      two side-by-side `.pane`s (analytics + Google). The wider
      container naturally scales the 6.2:1 banner and the identity
      row to YouTube's desktop proportions without page-specific CSS. %>
  <div class="pane-row">
    <div class="pane pane--wide">
      <%= render "channels/banner", channel: @channel %>

      <div class="channel-identity">
        <% if @channel.avatar_url.present? %>
          <%= image_tag @channel.avatar_url,
                        alt: "channel avatar",
                        class: "channel-avatar" %>
        <% else %>
          <div class="channel-avatar channel-avatar--placeholder text-muted"
               aria-label="no avatar">no avatar</div>
        <% end %>
        <div class="channel-headline">
          <div class="channel-headline__title"><%= display_title %></div>
          <div class="channel-headline__meta text-muted">
            <% if @channel.handle.present? %>
              <span class="channel-headline__handle"><%= @channel.handle %></span>
            <% else %>
              <span class="channel-headline__handle" aria-label="no handle">@—</span>
            <% end %>
            <span class="channel-headline__sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span class="channel-headline__stat"><%= formatted_subscriber_count(@channel) %> subscribers</span>
            <span class="channel-headline__sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span class="channel-headline__stat"><%= formatted_video_count(@channel) %> videos</span>
          </div>

          <%# Description — plain-text + auto-linked URLs. The helper
              runs input through `simple_format(sanitize: true)` which
              strips `<script>` and `<img onerror>` payloads before any
              URL rewriting happens. XSS-safe by construction. Lives
              inside the headline column so it stacks under the title /
              meta line, mirroring YouTube's right-of-avatar layout. %>
          <div class="channel-headline__description">
            <% description_html = channel_description_html(@channel) %>
            <% if description_html.present? %>
              <%= description_html %>
            <% else %>
              <p class="caption">no description yet.</p>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <%# 2026-05-11 — the `[YouTube]` / `[Studio]` outbound links
          moved into the H1 row at the top of the page. The detail
          pane is now identity → description → links cluster. %>

      <%= render "channels/links", channel: @channel %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%# Row 2 — analytics summary + per-channel Google management panel,
      side-by-side in a single pane-row (2026-05-11 follow-up — the
      two panes previously stacked vertically; the user wants the
      high-signal numbers and the OAuth plumbing on the same row).
      Analytics renders first so subscribers/views sit on the left;
      the Google panel sits to the right. The existing `.pane-row`
      grid handles wrapping at narrow viewports. The `videos` row
      was dropped from the analytics table (the dedicated videos
      table further down surfaces that count next to the `[see all
      videos]` link). NO inline sparkline (locked decision — avoid
      chartkick coupling on the show page).

      2026-05-11 (later) — each pane uses the plain `.pane` class
      (NOT `.pane--standalone`) so the workspace's vertical hairline
      kicks in between the two adjacent siblings. The detail pane in
      row 1 keeps `pane--standalone` because it stands alone (single
      pane spanning the row). (Pane backgrounds were dropped
      2026-05-20; the previous `--color-pane-bg-a/b` zebra rhythm
      is gone — adjacent panes are now separated by a single
      hairline.) %>
  <div class="pane-row">
    <div class="pane">
      <h2 style="margin: 0 0 8px 0;">analytics</h2>
      <table class="detail-table" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">
        <tr>
          <td class="text-muted" style="padding-right: 12px;">subscribers</td>
          <td><%= formatted_subscriber_count(@channel) %></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="text-muted" style="padding-right: 12px;">views</td>
          <td><%= formatted_view_count(@channel) %></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(
            label: "full analytics",
            href: channel_analytics_path(@channel)
          )) %>
    </div>
    <%= render "channels/google_panel", channel: @channel, youtube_connection: @youtube_connection %>
  </div>

  <%# Videos table (NOT a pane). Mirrors /videos column shape, scoped
      to this channel. Starred-first, then latest by
      COALESCE(published_at, created_at) DESC, capped at 30. The
      `[see all videos]` link is rendered only when the channel has
      more than 30 videos — at <=30 the table already shows everything.
  %>
  <%= render "channels/videos_table",
             channel: @channel,
             videos: @channel_videos,
             total: @channel_videos_total %>

  <% if @available_channels.any? %>
    <%= render "channels/add_pane_dialog", available_channels: @available_channels, current_ids: @channel.id.to_s %>
  <% end %>
</div>
